# The Vercel deploy only needs api/*.py (stdlib functions + model.json), public/ (frontend),
# requirements.txt and vercel.json. Everything else is excluded to keep the function small.
.venv/
data/
models/
src/
scripts/
slurm/
tests/
docs/
app/
notebooks/
reports/
Literature Review/
# Python-package markers: exclude so Vercel does NOT auto-detect a Python/FastAPI backend
# and look for a single ASGI entrypoint. pyproject.toml lists fastapi (optional-deps) and marks
# an installable package; without it Vercel treats api/*.py as classic serverless functions
# (stdlib only, empty requirements.txt) — the same path the working applet-material project uses.
pyproject.toml
setup.py
setup.cfg
environment.yml
requirements-dev.txt
*.pkl
*.parquet
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.git/
